cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analysing the structure of online conversations using temporal networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a novel method for analysing digital communication. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) in many studies of digital communication. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is a relevant category as the paper examines user behaviour in online conversations. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with analysing digital communication which could have implications for cybersecurity and privacy.
